OL,3,CHe lost his family, then his legs: One
OL,4,Cchild's experience in Gaza
OL,6,FAhmad's beloved grandparents are also
OL,7,Fkilled.
OL,9,FThere is no one left to explain to
OL,10,FAhmad what is happening as he is taken
OL,11,Fto the Indonesian hospital, in the
OL,12,FGaza strip, to be treated for his
OL,13,Finjuries, which are miraculously only
OL,14,Fminor.
OL,16,FOn the streets outside, the funerals
OL,17,Fof his family quickly take place as
OL,18,Fthe bodies of his parents are carried
OL,19,Fthrough the streets.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/14
