OL,3,CHe lost his family, then his legs: One
OL,4,Cchild's experience in Gaza
OL,6,FNuseirat, a small town 16 kilometres
OL,7,Fsouth, is one of the areas listed. So,
OL,8,Fnow in the care of two of his uncles,
OL,9,FIbrahim and Salah, the toddler is
OL,10,Ftaken there in a bid to seek safety.
OL,12,FOnce in Nuseirat, they take refuge in
OL,13,Fa UN-run school which has become home
OL,14,Fto hundreds of displaced Gazans.
OL,16,FWhen he cries out at night it is his
OL,17,Fyoungest uncle, Saleh, who comforts
OL,18,Fhim. The pair become inseparable.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/14
